 AS parts of efforts to eradicating poverty, the Redeemed Christian Church of God, (RCCG), Christ The Lord Parish, Lagos Province 20, Lekki, Lagos, Nigeria, has announced that it would be holding a women and youths empowerment programme. According to a statement made available to The Nation, by the Pastor Pastor-in-charge of Lagos Province 20, Pastor Tunde Netufo, the summit is titled “The Economies of the new Decade – The Winning Agenda.” “The Economic Summit will hold on Saturday February 22, 2020 at the Redeemed Christian Church of God, Christ The Lord Parish, 1-5, Admiralty Road, Lekki Phase 1, Lagos, Nigeria. The event will start by 9am prompt and end by 2:00pm. “The Keynote Speaker is Dr. ‘Biodun Adedipe. Dr. Adedipe is an accomplished trainer in the Nigerian banking and finance industry, and a highly sought-after analyst and commentator on government budgets and economic policies. Other speakers include Mrs. Uwa Osa-Oboh, Mr. Africanfarmer Mogaji, an agriculture expert and Dr. Chidi Okpaluba, who is an expert on SMEs.   